le of the twentieth century—all while raising two children, one with severe autism. Her story is full of strife and striving, but as an artist, Flack has always been able to find the beauty in it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aArt, AmericanzNew York (State)zNew Yorky20th century. 0aArtistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aPhoto-realismzUnited States. 0aWomen artistszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Artists, Architects, Photographers.2bisacsh  a10th Street Artists.  aAbstract Expressionism.  aAudrey Flack.  aBill De Kooning.  aCedarTavern.  aCooper Union.  aElaine de Kooning.  aGrace Hartigan.  aJackson Pollock.  aNew York Academy of Art.  aNew York Art Scene.  aPhillip Pearlstein.  aPost-war American Art.  aart.  aautism.  aautobiography.  afeminism.  amemoir.  amotherhood.  aphotorealism.  asculpture.  atwentieth century.  awomen.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079776340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271098302?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271098302423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271098302/original  a978-3-11-079776-3  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles